<p class="eyebrow">Software-defined networking</p>
<h1>VoiceTel SDN appliance</h1>
<p class="lede">Plug-and-play SIP traversal. Place a Raspberry Pi running our image in your LAN; it establishes an encrypted tunnel to VoiceTel. Your PBX registers locally and just works — no NAT headaches, no ALG fights, no firewall configuration.</p>

<p>Solves dropped calls, no audio, one-way audio, rejected calls — the symptoms of NAT, ALG, UDP timer, and general firewall misconfiguration. Optional in-call HA over redundant connectivity for business continuity.</p>

<p>Native integrations with Asterisk, FreePBX, FreeSWITCH, and FusionPBX.</p>

<p>Phase 1 placeholder. Full marketing page lands per the brief's <code>§7 /sdn/</code> spec; technical specification at <a href="http://sdn.voicetel.com">sdn.voicetel.com</a>.</p>

